    {
        "content": "<p>I think you'll have an easier time if you define your elementary row switch function using <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Equiv.Perm#doc\">docs#Equiv.Perm</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Matrix.submatrix#doc\">docs#Matrix.submatrix</a></p>",
        "id": 505472949,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Diamond",
        "timestamp": 1741884141
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Matrix.submatrix</code> represents a re-indexing, and <code>Equiv.Perm</code> controls that indexing</p>",
        "id": 505473148,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Diamond",
        "timestamp": 1741884198
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>also useful: <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Equiv.swap#doc\">docs#Equiv.swap</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Equiv.Perm.sign_swap#doc\">docs#Equiv.Perm.sign_swap</a></p>",
        "id": 505473759,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Diamond",
        "timestamp": 1741884359
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or just use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Matrix.swap#doc\">docs#Matrix.swap</a></p>",
        "id": 505473894,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1741884393
    },
